Title: DOOR / HATCH: REAR DOOR: REASSEMBLY; 2016 - 2022 MY Prius [11/2015 -        ]

REASSEMBLY

CAUTION / NOTICE / HINT

HINT:

  • Use the same procedure for the RH side and LH side.
  • The following procedure is for the LH side.

PROCEDURE

1. PRECAUTION

NOTICE:

After turning the power switch off, waiting time may be required before disconnecting the cable from the negative (-) auxiliary battery terminal. Therefore, make sure to read the disconnecting the cable from the negative (-) auxiliary battery terminal notices before proceeding with work.

10. INSTALL REAR DOOR NO. 3 WEATHERSTRIP

(a) Clean the rear door panel.

(b) Remove the release paper from a new rear door No. 3 weatherstrip.

HINT:

After removing the release paper, keep the exposed adhesive free from foreign matter.

(c) Engage the claw and install the rear door No. 3 weatherstrip.

Double-sided Tape

11. INSTALL REAR DOOR DUST PROOF SEAL

(a) Engage the 3 claws to install 3 new rear door dust proof seals.

12. INSTALL REAR DOOR PANEL CUSHION

(a) Engage the 2 claws to install a new rear door panel cushion.

13. INSTALL REAR DOOR OUTSIDE HANDLE FRAME SUB-ASSEMBLY

(a) Apply MP grease to the sliding parts of the rear door outside handle frame sub-assembly.

(b) Engage the claw as shown in the illustration.

*A

Outside

*B

Inside

(c) Using a T30 "TORX" socket wrench, install the rear door outside handle frame sub-assembly with the screw.

Torque:

4.0 N·m {41 kgf·cm, 35 in·lbf}

14. INSTALL REAR DOOR REAR OUTSIDE HANDLE PAD

(a) Engage the 3 guides and claw to install the rear door rear outside handle pad.

15. INSTALL REAR DOOR FRONT OUTSIDE HANDLE PAD

(a) Engage the 3 claws to install the rear door front outside handle pad.

16. INSTALL REAR DOOR OUTSIDE HANDLE COVER

(a) Engage the claw.

(b) Using a T30 "TORX" socket wrench, install the rear door outside handle cover with the screw.

Torque:

4.0 N·m {41 kgf·cm, 35 in·lbf}

17. INSTALL REAR DOOR OUTSIDE HANDLE ASSEMBLY

(a) Insert the front end of the rear door outside handle assembly into the rear door outside handle frame sub-assembly.

Install in this Direction

(b) Insert the rear end of the rear door outside handle assembly into the rear door outside handle frame sub-assembly, then slide the rear door outside handle assembly toward the front of the vehicle to install it.

(c) Move the lever as shown in the illustration and engage the 2 claws to secure the rear door outside handle assembly.

18. INSTALL REAR DOOR LOCK WITH MOTOR ASSEMBLY

Click here

19. INSTALL REAR DOOR WINDOW REGULATOR ASSEMBLY

(a) Apply MP grease to the sliding parts of the rear door window regulator assembly.

(b) Temporarily install the temporary bolt to the rear door window regulator assembly.

(c) Temporarily install the rear door window regulator assembly with the 3 bolts.

*a

Temporary Bolt

(d) Tighten the temporary bolt and 3 bolts to install the rear door window regulator assembly.

HINT:

Tighten the bolts in the order shown in the illustration.

Torque:

8.0 N·m {82 kgf·cm, 71 in·lbf}

(e) Connect the connector.

20. INSTALL REAR DOOR GLASS CHANNEL FILLER

(a) Apply soapy water to a new rear door glass channel filler.

(b) Install the rear door glass channel filler to the rear door glass sub-assembly at position shown in the illustration.

Standard Dimension

Area

Measurement

A

5.0 mm (0.197 in.)

B

5.0 mm (0.197 in.)

*A

*B

Rear Side

*a

Edge of curved surface

21. INSTALL REAR DOOR GLASS CHANNEL SUB-ASSEMBLY

(a) Apply soapy water to the channel filler side of the rear door glass channel sub-assembly.

(b) Using a plastic hammer, install the rear door glass channel sub-assembly to the position shown in the illustration.

Standard Dimension

Area

Measurement

A

5.0 mm (0.197 in.)

B

5.0 mm (0.197 in.)

NOTICE:

To prevent damaging the rear door glass sub-assembly, be careful not to strike the channel with too much force.

*A

Front Side

*B

Rear Side

*a

Edge of curved surface

22. INSTALL REAR DOOR GLASS SUB-ASSEMBLY

(a) Insert the rear door glass sub-assembly into the rear door panel as shown in the illustration.

NOTICE:

Do not damage the rear door glass sub-assembly.

Install in this Direction (1)

Install in this Direction (2)

(b) Slide the rear door glass sub-assembly to install it as shown in the illustration.

23. INSTALL REAR DOOR QUARTER WINDOW GLASS

(a) Install the rear door quarter window glass to the rear door quarter window weatherstrip.

(b) Install the rear door quarter window glass with rear door quarter window weatherstrip as shown in the illustration.

Install in this Direction

24. INSTALL REAR DOOR WINDOW DIVISION BAR SUB-ASSEMBLY

(a) Install the rear door window division bar sub-assembly with the screw and 2 bolts.

Screw

Bolt

Torque:

Screw :

3.1 N·m {32 kgf·cm, 27 in·lbf}

Bolt :

8.5 N·m {87 kgf·cm, 75 in·lbf}

25. INSTALL REAR DOOR WEATHERSTRIP

(a) Clean the rear door panel.

(b) Remove the release paper from a new rear door weatherstrip.

HINT:

After removing the release paper, keep the exposed adhesive free from foreign matter.

(c) Engage the 25 clips and install the rear door weatherstrip.

*a

Double-sided Tape

26. INSTALL REAR DOOR CHECK ASSEMBLY

(a) Apply MP grease to the sliding parts of the rear door check assembly.

(b) Clean the bolt hole in the vehicle body.

(c) Clean the threads of the bolt (B).

(d) Apply adhesive to the threads of the bolt (B).

Adhesive:

Toyota Genuine Adhesive 1324, Three Bond 1324 or equivalent

(e) Install the rear door check assembly with the 3 bolts.

Torque:

Bolt (A) :

5.5 N·m {56 kgf·cm, 49 in·lbf}

Bolt (B) :

30 N·m {306 kgf·cm, 22 ft·lbf}

27. INSTALL REAR DOOR GLASS RUN

(a) Install the rear door glass run.

28. INSTALL REAR DOOR NO. 2 SERVICE HOLE COVER

(a) Install the rear door No. 2 service hole cover.

29. INSTALL REAR DOOR PANEL PROTECTOR

(a) Install the rear door panel protector.

30. INSTALL REAR DOOR SERVICE HOLE COVER

(a) Apply new butyl tape to the rear door panel.

(b) Pass the rear door lock remote control cable assembly and rear door inside locking cable assembly through a new rear door service hole cover.

*a

Reference Point

(c) Attach the rear door service hole cover according to the reference points on the rear door panel.

NOTICE:

Securely install the rear door service hole cover preventing wrinkles and air bubbles.

31. INSTALL REAR DOOR FRAME GARNISH

(a) Engage the 2 claws to install the rear door frame garnish.

32. INSTALL REAR SPEAKER ASSEMBLY

Click here

33. INSTALL REAR DOOR INSIDE HANDLE SUB-ASSEMBLY

(a) Engage the 2 claws to install the rear door inside handle sub-assembly.

34. INSTALL REAR DOOR NO. 2 VENT SEAL

(a) Install the rear door No. 2 vent seal to the front door inner glass weatherstrip.

Install in this Direction

35. INSTALL REAR DOOR INNER GLASS WEATHERSTRIP WITH REAR DOOR NO. 2 VENT SEAL

(a) Install the rear door inner glass weatherstrip with rear door No. 2 vent seal as shown in the illustration.

Install in this Direction

36. INSTALL REAR DOOR TRIM BOARD SUB-ASSEMBLY

(a) Install the No. 1 door scuff plate clamp as shown in the illustration.

Install in this Direction

(b) Connect the rear door lock remote control cable assembly and rear door inside locking cable assembly to the rear door inside handle sub-assembly as shown in the illustration.

*1

Rear Door Inside Locking Cable Assembly

*2

Rear Door Lock Remote Control Cable Assembly

Install in this Direction

(c) Engage the 6 claws and guide.

(d) Engage the 8 clips to install the rear door trim board sub-assembly.

(e) Install the 3 screws.

37. INSTALL REAR POWER WINDOW REGULATOR SWITCH ASSEMBLY WITH REAR DOOR UPPER ARMREST BASE PANEL

(a) Connect the connector.

(b) Engage the 2 clips and 2 claws to install the rear power window regulator switch assembly with rear door upper armrest base panel as shown in the illustration.

Install in this Direction

38. INSTALL REAR ARMREST ASSEMBLY

(a) Engage the 3 clips and 7 claws to install the rear armrest assembly as shown in the illustration.

Install in this Direction

39. INSTALL REAR DOOR INSIDE HANDLE BEZEL PLUG

(a) Engage the 3 claws to install the rear door inside handle bezel plug.
